result.execSummary:
Daniel Edward Anderson was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Daniel Edward Anderson was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:38 Defendant Daniel Edward Anderson in court, in custody. Atty Liesl Nelson appeared with Def in court.  William H. Thorie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant has copy of complaint.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant. Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Nelson and Def state Def is willing to return to the State of MN. Nelson reviews Order with Def; Def willing to sign and waive his extradition rights. Def signs. Court states the Def has knowingly and willingly waived his right to extradition. Remand custody to PCSO to be delivered to MN.
